We’ve been working together to TNR a colony at an abandoned house! Trapping has been tricky since we do not have access to the property, so we have had to trap outside on the sidewalk. We were lucky and able to catch 10 cats for our big spay/neuter day last weekend! While we had originally thought there were only 10-15 cats, we have already TNRed 15. Now, we expect there are about 15+ to go. 

All of these cats were spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, flea treated, and ear tipped. No more babies for you! Happy life 🥰

I also saw three other cats hanging out with her - at least two of whom are male and not neutered. I want to trap them and get them fixed and find her kittens. Big Fudge is one of my cats at @lange_foundation. He looks and feels a little scraggly, but he is a giant ten-year-old baby who loves being pet. He meows for attention and is super friendly. He loves everyone and everyone loves him right back.  He is FIV+ but wouldn’t hurt a fly and gets along with other cats just fine. He is looking for a forever home in or around Los Angeles!

Yesterday we trapped 41 cats for spay neuter and this morning they are all getting fixed, microchipped, vaccinated, and flea treated! We caught 3 males with large wounds and at least 2 pregnant mamas. We are so happy we are able to get all these cats fixed and help prevent more kittens from being born outside! If you’d like to donate to our TNR fund you can do so at Langefoundation.org/donate 🐱
